Metadata: The valdivones, anti-​inflammatory diterpene esters from the South African soft coral "Alcyonium valdivae"

The South African soft coral "Alcyonium valdivae" contains five diterpene esters, valdivones A and B, the corresponding methoxy ketals, and dihydrovaldivon​e A. Although the producing organisms are unrelated taxonomically, the valdivones are most closely related to the sarcodictins from the stoloniferan coral "Sarcodictyon roseum". Valdivones A and B inhibit chemically- induced inflammation in the mouse ear assay.
